JOHNSON v. UNITED STATES. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Eighth Circuit. January 5, 1915.) No. 4246. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the Eastern District of Oklahoma. James C. Denton, of Muskogee, Okl., for plaintiff in error. D. H. Linebaugh, U. S. Atty., of Atoka, Okl., C. O. Herndon, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Tulson, Okl., and W. P. McGinnis, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Muskogee, Okl., for the United States.

Before HOOK and OAKLAND, Circuit Judges, and AMIDON, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Reversed, without costs to either party in this court, upon the confession of error and consent of defendant in error, and cause remanded, with directions to sustain demurrer to indictment.
